  "prompt": "What universities does GAIN Capital recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "GAIN Capital, a financial services firm, typically recruits from a variety of universities, specifically those known for strong programs in finance, economics, business administration, computer science, and data analytics. While the specific universities may vary from year to year and depend on current hiring needs, GAIN Capital often targets reputable institutions known for producing graduates with relevant skills.\n\nAs for majors, GAIN Capital particularly looks for candidates with degrees in:\n\n- Finance\n- Economics\n- Business Administration\n- Computer Science\n- Mathematics\n- Statistics\n- Data Science\n- Engineering (often related to analytics or quantitative fields)\n\nCandidates with strong analytical skills, quantitative backgrounds, and knowledge of financial markets are highly valued. For the most accurate and current information regarding their recruitment practices, it's advisable to check GAIN Capital's official careers page or reach out to their human resources department.",
